        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10113",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In-memory segment creation  is not significant without segment mergin functionality",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-21T10:50:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-21T10:50:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11019",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No, it's Zend_Search issue, which doesn't depends from Zend_Memory.\n\nZend_Memory goal is to use filesystem (or other backend) as a temporary storage for data, when we don't have enough memory.\n\nmemory segmen storage provider is a 'virtual filesystem' in RAM. Goal is to speed up document indexing, which performs a lot of small read\/write operations.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-10-20T11:11:09.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-10-20T11:11:09.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11392",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing fix version to 0.6.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-13T15:17:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-13T15:17:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12361",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "obsolete.\n\nZend_Search_Lucene uses MaxBufferedDocs option to accumulate documents in memory.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-24T19:50:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-24T19:50:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30407",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chrismattmann",
                        "name": "chrismattmann",
                        "displayName": "Chris Mattmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\n\nIn the case where there is a separate Lucene index, built from e.g., Java Lucene, then wouldn't a Zend_Search_Lucene RAMDirectory that loads that separately created index into memory and then supports querying of it as persisted in RAM significantly speed up the performance of ZSL?\n\nI can see how MaxBufferedDocs affects indexing performance, but how does it affect search performance?\n\nThanks,\nChris\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chrismattmann",
                        "name": "chrismattmann",
                        "displayName": "Chris Mattmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-24T19:53:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-24T19:53:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35818",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Chris, I've just got your comment. MaxBufferedDocs doesn't affect search performance. But Java Lucene RAMDirectory implementation also used only during indexing. OS supported RAM disk or OS level file system caching may be used to increase search performance.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-06T03:26:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-06T03:26:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35840",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chrismattmann",
                        "name": "chrismattmann",
                        "displayName": "Chris Mattmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for your comment, Alexander. Is an OS supported RAM disk or OS level file system caching something that we could implement in Zend_Search_Lucene? I'm willing to help, just point me in the right direction...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chrismattmann",
                        "name": "chrismattmann",
                        "displayName": "Chris Mattmann",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-07T08:46:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-07T08:46:03.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
